attributes.text:
@notice get cover data
 @param tokenId cover token id

@notice Switch NexusMutual membership to `newAddress`.
 @param newAddress address

@notice Set if buyCover calls are allowed (true) or not (false).
 @param _buysAllowed value set for buysAllowed

@notice Set treasury address where `buyCover` distributor fees and `ethOut` from `sellNXM` are sent.
 @param _treasury new treasury address
@dev required to be allow for receiving ETH claim payouts

baseURI().details: Returns the base URI set via {_setBaseURI}. This will be automatically added as a prefix in {tokenURI} to each token's URI, or to the token ID if no specific URI is set for that token ID.

buyCover(address,address,uint256,uint16,.details: buy cover for a coverable identified by its contractAddress

params.coverAsset: asset of the premium and of the sum assured.
params.coverType: cover type dermining how the data parameter is decoded
params.data: abi-encoded field with additional cover data fields
params.maxPriceWithFee: max price (including fee) to be spent on the cover.
params.sumAssured: amount payable if claim is submitted and considered valid

executeCoverAction(uint256,uint256,addre.details: The purpose of this function is future-proofing for updates to the cover buy->claim cycle.

params.asset: optional asset to be transferred along with the action executed
params.assetAmount: optional asset amount to be transferred along with the action executed

returns.response: (abi-encoded response, amount withheld from the original asset amount supplied)

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBaseURI(string).details: Function to set the base URI for all token IDs. It is automatically added as a prefix to the value returned in {tokenURI}, or to the token ID if {tokenURI} is empty.

params.data: abi-encoded field with additional claim data fields

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: See {IERC165-supportsInterface}. Time complexity O(1), guaranteed to always use less than 30 000 gas.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

approveNXM(address,uint256).notice: Set `amount` as the allowance of `spender` over the distributor's NXM tokens.

executeCoverAction(uint256,uint256,addre.notice: Execute an action on specific cover token. The action is identified by an `action` id. Allows for an ETH transfer or an ERC20 transfer. If less than the supplied assetAmount is needed, it is returned to `msg.sender`.

getPayoutOutcome(uint256).notice: get state of a claim payout. Returns status of cover,  amount paid as part of the payout, address of the cover asset)

redeemClaim(uint256,uint256).notice: Redeem the claim to the cover. Requires that that the payout is completed.

sellNXM(uint256,uint256).notice: Sell Distributor-owned NXM tokens for ETH

setBuysAllowed(bool).notice: Set if buyCover calls are allowed (true) or not (false).

setFeePercentage(uint256).notice: Set fee percentage for buyCover premiums.  `_feePercentage` has 2 decimals of precision ( 5000 is 50%)

setTreasury(address).notice: Set treasury address where `buyCover` distributor fees and `ethOut` from `sellNXM` are sent.

submitClaim(uint256,bytes).notice: Submit a claim for the cover

withdrawNXM(address,uint256).notice: Moves `amount` tokens from the distributor to `recipient`.
